'''Force bellow''' was a [[Force power/Legends|power]] in which the [[Force-sensitive/Legends|user]] would amplify their voice using [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], to communicate better,<ref name="Darth Plagueis novel">[[Darth Plagueis (novel)|''Darth Plagueis'']]</ref> or to attack.<ref name="Chapter 24 Star Wars: Clone Wars">{{CW|24}}</ref>

The [[Clone madness|mentally unstable]] [[Cloning/Legends|clone]] of a [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Joruus C'baoth]] used this power while on board [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn's]] [[Flagship/Legends|command ship]], the [[Chimaera/Legends|''Chimaera'']]. C'baoth usually startled [[Gilad Pellaeon/Legends|Gilad Pellaeon]], the [[Captain/Legends|captain]] of the [[Starship/Legends|ship]], as he entered the bridge bellowing Thrawn's name.

[[Ithorian/Legends|Ithorian]] [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] were capable of using this power as well, amplifying their voices to immense proportions to destroy obstructions. The Ithorian Jedi [[Roron Corobb/Legends|Roron Corobb]] was one who used this technique in combat during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. He used it against [[General/Legends|General]] [[Grievous/Legends|Grievous]] while protecting [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]].

